{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88d987ac-1475-4976-87e7-1fe0ed11aa89","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by swapping the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_km65nsgkavleOnapNTpNLA","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7091f974b6904d0eb2cf54dc1c957603/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7091f974b6904d0eb2cf54dc1c957603/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f5d526e1-a383-4d33-8d81-61d848ed408f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":368,"requestId":"5C17:3113E4:1DFA6DD:21C830F:6A07C84E"},"id":"2a853a15-476f-4e99-a45e-063de3f747e4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:28:53.717Z","parentId":"8da12a1c-d15a-47ca-b442-08eea89518bb"}
